(285, 1, '2017-04-04 11:42:10', '2017-04-04 11:42:10', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_raw_html][/vc_raw_html][vc_column_text el_class="faq_title"]FAQ/Contact[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class="faq_main_text"]We’d Love to hear from you – please fill in the following form[/vc_column_text][contact-form-7 id="21" title="faq_contact_form"][vc_separator el_class="faq_separator"][vc_column_text el_class="faq_under_title"]Frequently Asked Questions[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class="faq_main_text_second"]Taco, Beer, Tequila Festival - DC\'s 1st Taco Festival - is Saturday, July 15th, 2017 at The Yards Park Lot H/I - literally across the street from Nat\'s Stadium! Be sure to review the questions and answers below for the most up-to-date information on this year’s event!\n\n-Location: Capitol Riverfront - The Yards Park Lot H/I, 136 N Street SE, Washington, DC 20003\n\n-Date &amp; Time: Saturday, July 15th, 2017 - 2 Sessions (Tickets are for a Single Session) Session 1: VIP 11 am - 3 pm/All Other Tickets Noon - 3 pm; Session 2: VIP 5 mm - 9 pm/All Other Tickets 6 pm - 9 pm\n\n-Ticket Information: YOU MUST BE 21 YEARS OLD TO ATTEND - NO EXCEPTIONS..Your tickets will NOT be mailed to you, you should bring a printed copy of the email confirmation that you received when you placed your order and You MUST HAVE A VALID ID AND OF LEGAL DRINKING AGE (21 OR OLDER) TO ATTEND THE EVENT. Will call is at the event entrance on the day of the event, you’ll see signs and tents. General Admission Ticket and VIP Tickets INCLUDE unlimited wine samples to taste at the event – PLEASE DRINK RESPONSIBILY!\n\n-Box Office &amp; Taco/Beer/Tequila Tasting Times (Note: Tickets are for a Single Session): VIP Access for Tacos and Tastings (unlimited beer and Tequila tastings at the Tequila Pavilion are included in VIP Ticket Price) - Session 1: 11 am - 3 pm/Session 2: 5 pm - 9 pm; General Admission and Tequila Tasting Tickets - Session 1: Noon - 3 pm/Session 2: 6 pm - 9 pm;\n\n-Metro and Parking Access: Nearby Metro Entrances: Navy Yard Metro (Green Line): New Jersey Avenue Entrance - 1101 New Jersey Avenue SE (943 feet N), Navy Yard Metro (Green Line): M Street Entrance - 55 M Street SE (1005 feet NW);\n\nNearby Public Parking: The Yards Lot F - 136 N Street SE (289 feet NW), Nats Lot C - Garage Parking - 1500 South Capitol Street SE (498 feet W), The Yards Lot L - 285 Tingey Street SE (686 feet E), THERE IS NO GUARANTEE OF PARKING AVAILABILITY..\n\n-Food: 20+ Taco Trucks/Taqueria Restaurants EACH will have at least one $3/Taco Option (Use your Taco Ticket - you get 5 with your Ticket Purchase - you can also purchase Tacos/Food directly from Food Vendors or purchase Additional Taco Tickets) and 2+ more taco options - more than 60+ Taco variations to choose from. VEGETARIAN AND VEGAN OPTIONS WILL BE PROVIDED BY SELECT VENDORS (Taco Menu will be provided at event the day of event).\n\n-Hot Sauce and Other Food Items will be available to purchase with cash or cre\n\n-Beer: Unlimited Craft Beer from over 30+ Breweries and over 60+ beers is included in your ticket price - PLEASE DRINK RESPONSIBLY;\n\n-Tequila Pavilion: (Note this is accessible/available ONLY to "Tequila Tasting" and "VIP" Ticket Purchasers) - 10+ Tequila/Mezcal Producers sampling over 30+ Tequilas/Mezcals (tickets are limited) - PLEASE DRINK RESPONSIBLY;\n\n-VIP Tent Includes early access to the Festival (1 hour longer tastings), Private Bathrooms, Private Tent, Limited Seating, Rare Tequila/Mezcal Tasting and Access to all other Festival tents and amenities (VIP Ticket includes Tequila Pavilion tasting/access);\n\n-Margarita Stations are spread throughout the Festival Venue - a selection of margaritas will be available for $6/cash or credit OR you can use 2 "Taco Tickets" per Margarita - this is separate from access to the Tequila Pavilion - PLEASE DRINK RESPONSIBLY;\n\n–ATM’s – Yes, we will have them on site, but most vendors will take credit card – still, it’s always smart for you to have a little cash on hand!\n\n-Children: NO ONE UNDER 21 YEARS OLD WILL HAVE ACCESS TO THIS EVENT - THANKS IN ADVANCE FOR YOUR UNDERSTANDING!\n\n-Designated Driver: ONLY PURCHASED CASH DAY OF EVENT - With a Designated Driver ticket, you will be wrist-banded differently and will not be able to taste or purchase any alcoholic beverages.\n\n-Dogs/Pets: NO PETS. Service dogs are welcome but must register in advance and onsite upon arrival with all proper documentation.\n\nNO PETS, NO UNAUTHORIZED VENDING, NO OUTSIDE ALCOHOL,\n\nNO ILLEGAL SUBSTANCES, NO EXCEPTIONS![/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'FAQ/Contact', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '81-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-04-04 11:42:10', '2017-04-04 11:42:10', '', 81, 'http://fest.dev/2017/04/04/81-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(286, 1, '2017-04-04 10:27:06', '2017-04-04 10:27:06', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_raw_html][/vc_raw_html][vc_column_text el_class="faq_title"]FAQ/Contact[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class="faq_main_text"]We’d Love to hear from you – please fill in the following form[/vc_column_text][contact-form-7 id="21" title="faq_contact_form"][vc_separator el_class="faq_separator"][vc_column_text el_class="faq_under_title"]Frequently Asked Questions[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class="faq_main_text_second"]Taco, Beer, Tequila Festival - DC\'s 1st Taco Festival - is Saturday, July 15th, 2017 at The Yards Park Lot H/I - literally across the street from Nat\'s Stadium! Be sure to review the questions and answers below for the most up-to-date information on this year’s event!\r\n\r\n-Location: Bull Run Regional Park Special Events Center – Click here for Location/Directions\r\n\r\n-Date &amp; Time: Saturday, July 15th, 2017 - 2 Sessions (Tickets are for a Single Session) Session 1: VIP 11 am - 3 pm/All Other Tickets Noon - 3 pm; Session 2: VIP 5 mm - 9 pm/All Other Tickets 6 pm - 9 pm\r\n\r\n-Ticket Information: YOU MUST BE 21 YEARS OLD TO ATTEND - NO EXCEPTIONS..Your tickets will NOT be mailed to you, you should bring a printed copy of the email confirmation that you received when you placed your order and You MUST HAVE A VALID ID AND OF LEGAL DRINKING AGE (21 OR OLDER) TO ATTEND THE EVENT. Will call is at the event entrance on the day of the event, you’ll see signs and tents. General Admission Ticket and VIP Tickets INCLUDE unlimited wine samples to taste at the event – PLEASE DRINK RESPONSIBILY!\r\n\r\n-Box Office &amp; Taco/Beer/Tequila Tasting Times (Note: Tickets are for a Single Session): VIP Access for Tacos and Tastings (unlimited beer and Tequila tastings at the Tequila Pavilion are included in VIP Ticket Price) - Session 1: 11 am - 3 pm/Session 2:, Noon for General Admission and end at 5:30 p.m. on Saturday and Sunday (30 minutes before the end of the Festival). Unopened Bottles and Case SALES continue through close (6 p.m. on Saturday &amp; Sunday).\r\n\r\n-Parking Access: The parking lot gates will open at 10 a.m. and close at 8 p.m. on both Saturday and Sunday.\r\n\r\n-Food: Yes! But it’s not included in your ticket price – we will not only have food trucks and gourmet food vendors (we take food choices very seriously!), but there will be the VA Oyster Pavilion with both fresh shucked oysters and oysters prepared in various dishes (Menu Soon..).\r\n\r\n–ATM’s – Yes, we will have them on site, but most vendors will take credit card – still, it’s always smart for you to have a little cash on hand!\r\n\r\n-Children: Children are welcome at the event and there is a large ‘Children’s Area’ with entertainment and more!\r\n\r\n-Designated Driver: With a Designated Driver ticket, you will be wrist-banded differently and will not be able to taste or purchase wine.\r\n\r\n-Dogs/Pets: No pets. Service dogs are welcome but must register in advance and onsite upon arrival with all proper documentation.\r\n\r\n-Things you can bring:\r\n\r\nBlankets &amp; Chairs are welcomed and encouraged. Coolers are welcome but you can NOT bring your own alcohol or anything illegal in the state of Virginia. All bags and coolers are subject to search by our security team. Feel free to bring your own non-alcoholic beverages and snacks for the day. Patrons are welcome to bring reasonably sized outdoor shade canopies to Virginia Wine Festival.\r\n\r\nNO PETS, NO UNAUTHORIZED VENDING, NO OUTSIDE ALCOHOL,\r\n\r\nNO ILLEGAL SUBSTANCES, NO EXCEPTIONS![/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'FAQ/Contact', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '81-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-04-04 10:27:06', '2017-04-04 10:27:06', '', 81, 'http://fest.dev/2017/04/04/81-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
